title: For Sale:  S&W 29-3 8 3/8" .44 Magnum, Rare 1988 Variation
postcontent: This is a rare early S&W 29-3 .44 Magnum revolver with an 8 3/8" barrel factory broached to accommodate the S&W scope mounting system. This configuration is identified in the Standard catalog of Smith & Wesson as the Model 29-4, with Product Code 101233, manufactured in 1989 with factory rings and square-butt Combat Grips. The Smith in this auction is an earlier uncatalogued Model 29-3, made in 1988 (even the accompanying Scope Mount Installation Procedure card is dated 06/88). This is a 6-shot, N-frame revolver with Wide Target color case hardened Hammer and Trigger, white outline adjustable rear sight, red ramp insert front sight, 8 3/8" barrel with already described scope mounting system with rings, and beautiful rare square-butt Combat Grips. As it was made in 1988, it has desirable features no longer found on current Smiths: It has the square butt grip frame with wood grips, the firing pin is on the hammer, and there is no lock (new Smiths have round-butt frames with rubber grips, internal firing pins, and keyed locks that disable the firearm when turned to the lock position). It is in excellent used condition with few handling marks and very little bluing wear (there is a small area on the right side of the barrel towards the muzzle as shown in the pics). Additionally, there are powder burn marks in the bluing on the outside of the cylinder towards the front, corresponding to each chamber hole, from firing the weapon some time in the past. Please refer to the many detailed pics. Comes as shown with a Smith box not serial numbered to the gun, rings, manual, Scope Mount Installation Procedure card, and a bag of the self adhesive non-slip pads that are mentioned in the procedure card (probably a pretty rare factory item these days).
